01:15:02,896 --> 01:15:05,620
To those who long to be manly,

835
01:15:05,621 --> 01:15:07,237
to be true,

836
01:15:07,238 --> 01:15:09,356
to be what men should be.

837
01:15:09,356 --> 01:15:11,556
Stop it, Tom!

838
01:15:12,067 --> 01:15:15,362
Come to work as free men

839
01:15:15,362 --> 01:15:16,392
for each other.

840
01:15:16,393 --> 01:15:18,745
This isn't a bloody game!

841
01:15:18,745 --> 01:15:21,837
Whatever it is,
I don't want it!

842
01:15:21,838 --> 01:15:23,697
I don't want what you want!

843
01:15:23,698 --> 01:15:24,830
I don't care if it's yours,

844
01:15:24,832 --> 01:15:27,962
and I don't care
who Jimmy gives it to!

845
01:15:27,963 --> 01:15:30,354
I don't want it.

846
01:15:33,503 --> 01:15:35,041
Sarah.

847
01:15:35,503 --> 01:15:36,936
The bloody dog!

848
01:15:36,938 --> 01:15:38,253
[Grunts]

849
01:15:39,007 --> 01:15:41,807
[Shouting]

850
01:15:47,751 --> 01:15:50,086
[Grunts]

851
01:16:25,945 --> 01:16:28,555
[Breathing heavily]

852
01:16:50,922 --> 01:16:52,856
[Sobs]

853
01:16:52,858 --> 01:16:55,695
[Shouting]

854
01:17:24,665 --> 01:17:27,297
[Gasping]

855
01:17:37,391 --> 01:17:40,180
[Thunder crashes]

856
01:18:04,203 --> 01:18:06,397
What were you thinking,

857
01:18:07,293 --> 01:18:09,726
you dumb bastard?

858
01:19:20,844 --> 01:19:23,580
I've come for my father.

859
01:19:33,594 --> 01:19:35,795
Here.

860
01:19:45,658 --> 01:19:47,656
[Grunts]

861
01:19:49,570 --> 01:19:51,719
[Breathing heavily]

862
01:19:52,614 --> 01:19:54,881
The future.

863
01:20:29,922 --> 01:20:33,383
Your father's good as dead.

864
01:20:35,477 --> 01:20:37,311
So are you.

865
01:20:40,696 --> 01:20:43,031
[Grunts]

866
01:20:59,032 --> 01:21:02,133
[Grunting and gurgling]

867
01:21:47,562 --> 01:21:48,140
[Groaning]

868
01:21:48,140 --> 01:21:49,553
Dad!

869
01:21:51,187 --> 01:21:52,889
Dad!

870
01:21:52,890 --> 01:21:54,734
No!

871
01:21:55,288 --> 01:21:56,101
Dad.

872
01:21:56,101 --> 01:21:58,969
- [Groaning]
- Dad!

873
01:22:03,155 --> 01:22:04,596
[Grunting]

874
01:24:07,913 --> 01:24:09,844
Tom?

875
01:24:12,460 --> 01:24:14,229
Tom.

876
01:24:17,101 --> 01:24:18,914
Where are you going?

877
01:24:19,327 --> 01:24:21,273
Where's your father?

878
01:24:22,804 --> 01:24:25,283
Struth, what happened to you?

879
01:24:43,093 --> 01:24:44,901
Money.

880
01:24:47,366 --> 01:24:49,833
Listen, all right?

881
01:24:50,007 --> 01:24:52,608
You find anything, Tom?

882
01:24:52,610 --> 01:24:54,335
The ground right near you?

883
01:24:54,336 --> 01:24:56,444
The river?

884
01:24:57,570 --> 01:24:59,319
Got to look out for this lot.

885
01:24:59,687 --> 01:25:02,343
They'd be all over you
if you did.

886
01:25:02,343 --> 01:25:04,648
You want to keep quiet about it.

887
01:25:05,405 --> 01:25:07,805
Bloody scavengers.

888
01:25:08,835 --> 01:25:12,858
You've already been through
hard enough trouble as it is.

889
01:25:19,843 --> 01:25:21,795
So did you?

890
01:25:23,569 --> 01:25:26,202
You find the yellow stuff?

891
01:25:45,921 --> 01:25:48,179
Mr. Connolly.

892
01:25:49,275 --> 01:25:51,742
Thank you, Charlie.

893
01:26:00,945 --> 01:26:03,780
Go on.
Help yourself.

894
01:26:06,538 --> 01:26:08,172
[Sighs]

895
01:26:08,991 --> 01:26:11,538
I don't know
what's happening, Tom.

896
01:26:11,538 --> 01:26:14,180
I hope your father's all right.

897
01:26:14,956 --> 01:26:16,584
He's a good man.

898
01:26:16,585 --> 01:26:18,562
Got belief.

899
01:26:18,562 --> 01:26:21,942
A man's not a man
without conviction.

900
01:26:24,991 --> 01:26:26,249
See all this?

901
01:26:26,249 --> 01:26:30,359
All this industry going on here,

902
01:26:30,359 --> 01:26:32,993
I made it happen.

903
01:26:36,429 --> 01:26:39,139
This is our security.

904
01:26:43,132 --> 01:26:45,597
You ever felt it, Tom?

905
01:26:46,234 --> 01:26:47,725
The land?

906
01:26:47,726 --> 01:26:49,616
Hmm?

907
01:26:50,702 --> 01:26:52,193
[Chuckles]

908
01:26:57,906 --> 01:27:04,412
There's been a rumor
going around the camp.

909
01:27:04,413 --> 01:27:08,781
They say you, uh,
found some gold.

910
01:27:08,781 --> 01:27:11,615
On the farm, was it?

911
01:27:15,007 --> 01:27:18,382
If these buggers get it
in their head there's gold,

912
01:27:18,383 --> 01:27:22,767
they'll be up and off,
and that'll be that.

913
01:27:23,855 --> 01:27:26,256
You don't want that, Tom,

914
01:27:26,257 --> 01:27:28,421
these bastards
helping themselves,

915
01:27:28,422 --> 01:27:29,968
running all over your farm,

916
01:27:29,968 --> 01:27:31,960
helping themselves
to what's yours.

917
01:27:31,961 --> 01:27:33,026
Hmm?

918
01:27:33,898 --> 01:27:36,053
[Chuckles]

919
01:27:43,974 --> 01:27:47,031
If you've got nowhere
to go, son,

920
01:27:47,031 --> 01:27:49,619
you can come and stay with me.

921
01:27:50,133 --> 01:27:52,834
A boy needs a place to be,

922
01:27:52,835 --> 01:27:56,139
something to be certain of.

923
01:27:58,573 --> 01:28:02,577
Well, you ever think about it,

924
01:28:02,577 --> 01:28:04,522
just let me know

925
01:28:04,523 --> 01:28:06,656
when you're ready.

926
01:28:06,657 --> 01:28:09,124
Take your time.

927
01:28:13,734 --> 01:28:16,162
If it's not there, Tom,

928
01:28:16,163 --> 01:28:18,564
you can tell me.

929
01:28:19,468 --> 01:28:21,503
Is it true, Tom?

930
01:28:23,741 --> 01:28:26,343
Is it true?

931
01:28:42,312 --> 01:28:46,662
I'm just trying
to keep the dream alive, Tom.

932
01:28:46,663 --> 01:28:49,497
That's all I'm doing.

933
01:28:49,741 --> 01:28:52,210
You got a dream, son?

934
01:28:54,929 --> 01:28:56,923
Yes.

935
01:28:58,079 --> 01:29:00,514
And what is it?

936
01:29:10,577 --> 01:29:14,046
[Pensive piano music]

937
01:31:48,388 --> 01:31:51,412
Whoa. Whoa.

938
01:31:56,498 --> 01:31:58,866
You all right, son?

939
01:35:45,650 --> 01:35:47,150
The End

940
